title: Marshfield's key prep events this week
text:
Marshfield's key prep events this week Mark Massoglia , Daily Tribune Media 1:47 p.m. CDT October 18, 2015 File photo. CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Volleyball: Division 3 regional quarterfinal: Necedah at Spencer, 7 p.m. Tuesday: The four-time Cloverbelt Conference champion Spencer Rockets begin their tournament trail as the No. 1 seed in its regional. The goal will be to get back to state for the first time since 2011, when the Rockets brought home the silver trophy. Loyal/Granton is the No. 2 seed and Auburndale is seeded third in the tough regional. 
Football: Level 1 playoff game: Merrill at Medford, 7 p.m. Friday: The Raiders are co-Great Northern Conference champs with Antigo and garnered a No. 2. seed despite a Week 5 19-12 loss to Merrill, so the 2-7 seed matchup might be one of the best in the bracket. Medford's Conrad Bolz and Josh Thiede have 1,375 yards and 17 touchdowns combined for the year. Merrill had four running backs with at least 400 yards; Drew Hoff leads the way with 540 yards and nine TDs. 
Cross country: Division 2 Black River Falls sectional, 11 a.m. at Skyline Golf Course: Loyal/Greenwood/Granton senior Jarod Rudolph is the one to watch as he enters the sectional meet. He was the sectional runner-up last year and placed eight in the Division 2 competition at the state meet. Teams from Colby/Abbotsford, Adams-Friendship and Nekoosa/Port Edwards are also competing at Skyline Country Club. Read or Share this story: http://wrtnews.co/1LDSXWy TOP VIDEOS
